- Writing notes on Index cards help with remembering something. Spaced repetition is important. 
- Create meaningful groups that simplify the materials (Ex: abbreviations, numbers, etc)

- Memory Palace Technique: Call to mind the place you are familiar with, and it becomes a notepad. 
Add items around the home (mentally).

- Memory tricks help to move info into Long Term Memory. 
The more creative your memory tricks are, the more powerful it is, and easier to remember. 

Tips to help improve learning:
- New neurons are born every day in the hippocampus. 
1. Physical exercise helps new neurons survive. Exercise is very effective and benefits all of your vital organs. 
2. Eye exercises (practice looking at 3d images)
